<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:52PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Oconee,
southeastern Barrow, northwestern Clarke, northeastern Walton and
southeastern Jackson Counties through 515 PM EDT...
At 452 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Gratis, or near Monroe,
moving northeast at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Winder, Monroe, Statham, Arcade, Bogart, North High Shoals,
Bethlehem, Good Hope, Athens-Clarke County, Westgate Park, Bear Creek
Reservoir, Eastville, Nicholasville, Campton, Gratis and Beechwood
Hills.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
